content: * *Lau Teik Oon** was [Archdeacon](/wiki/Archdeacon) of [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) from 1967 to 1976. He was [ordained](/wiki/Ordained) in 1956 for the [Diocese](/wiki/Diocese) of [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) and later became [Vicar](/wiki/Vicar) of St John, [Jurong](/wiki/Jurong). He was an [Honorary Canon](/wiki/Canon_(priest)) of [St Andrew's Cathedral, Singapore](/wiki/St_Andrew%27s_Cathedral,_Singapore) from 1965. He died on 28 July 2011. This Singaporean biographical article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. - v - t - e
title: Lau Teik Oon
